20delivery%20of%20government%20services.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDey%20is%20the%20co-founder%20of%20Mazdoor%20Kisan%20Shakti%20Sangathan%20(MKSS)%2C%20which%20has%20led%20transparency%20and%20anti-corruption%20movements%20in%20India.%20The%20organisation%20is%20primarily%20based%20in%20Rajasthan%20that%20has%20led%20workers%E2%80%99%20and%20peasants%E2%80%99%20struggles%20for%20minimum%20wages%20and%20transparency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%20on%20December%207%2C%20the%20US%20State%20Department%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.state.gov%2Frecognizing-the-2023-anti-corruption-champions%2F%3Fs%3D31%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CFor%20the%20past%2035%20years%2C%20activist%20Nikhil%20Dey%20has%20championed%20policy%20reforms%20to%20empower%20workers%20in%20India.%20He%20and%20his%20counterparts%20have%20brought%20to%20light%20official%20corruption%2C%20such%20as%20the%20underpayment%20of%20workers%20on%20official%20projects%2C%20and%20built%20peasant%20and%20worker%20empowerment%20campaigns%20targeting%20corruption%20in%20the%20delivery%20of%20government%20services.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUS%20secretary%20of%20state%20Antony%20Blinken%20praised%C2%A0Dey%20for%20%E2%80%9Cworking%20with%20and%20for%20those%20harmed%20by%20corruption%2C%20and%20those%20particularly%20who%20are%20harmed%20most%20by%20it%3A%20underserved%2C%20marginalised%20populations%E2%80%9D.%20Blinken%20said%20Dey%20has%20helped%20communities%20in%20Rajasthan%20demand%20access%20to%20essential%20services%20and%20rights%20such%20as%20education%2C%20healthcare%2C%20fair%20wages%20and%20better%20working%20conditions.%20%E2%80%9CHis%20organization%20pioneered%20the%20practice%20of%20public%20audits%2C%20in%20which%20local%20officials%20have%20to%20report%20to%20communities%20how%20and%20where%20they%20spend%20the%20resources%2C%20and%20citizens%20have%20a%20chance%20themselves%20to%20ask%20probing%20questions%20of%20these%20officials%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20continued.%20These%20public%20audits%20spread%20across%20India%20and%20more%20citizens%20started%20taking%20the%20lead%20in%20holding%20officials%20to%20account%2C%20which%20%E2%80%9Cat%20its%20heart%2C%20is%20how%20democracy%20needs%20to%20work%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20award%2C%20set%20up%20in%202021%2C%20recognises%20the%20US%20government%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Csupport%20for%20anticorruption%20leaders%20who%20put%20their%20lives%20on%20the%20line%20to%20spur%20lasting%20change%E2%80%9D.%20Dey%20is%20the%20first%20Indian%20to%20receive%20the%20award.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%2010%20other%20International%20Anti-Corruption%20Champions%20for%202023%20recognised%20by%20the%20US%20government%20on%20Thursday%20were%20Stanislau%20Ivashkevich%20of%20Belarus%2C%20Jean-Claude%20Mputu%20of%20the%20Democratic%20Republic%20of%20the%20Congo%2C%20Arturo%20Torres%20of%20Ecuador%2C%20Ali%20(Mukhammedali)%20Toktakunov%20of%20Kyrgyz%20Republic%2C%20Marc%20N.%20Kollie%20of%20Liberia%2C%20Veronica%20Mihailov-Moraru%20of%20Moldova%2C%20Vladimir%20Novovic%20of%20Montenegro%2C%20Annette%20Planells%20of%20Panama%2C%20Francisco%20Belo%20Simoes%20da%20Costa%20of%20Timor-Leste%2C%20and%20May%20De%20Silva%20of%20Seychelles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F09114902%2FDIPNOTE-RESIZING-2.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F09114902%2FDIPNOTE-RESIZING-2.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F09114902%2FDIPNOTE-RESIZING-2-300x150.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F09114902%2FDIPNOTE-RESIZING-2-1024x512.png%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F0